<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-09-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-09-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="429" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d429">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/899.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                Minister</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-09-30">
                                    <hi rend="italic">September 30, 1913</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department suggests a written agreement covering every point agreed upon
                            and bearing the signatures of the contending factions, witnessed by you
                            or commander of battleships, as tending to impress on all concerned the
                            solemnity of the agreement.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Osborne</hi>.</signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>